  "name": "Indus Phase-33 T7 — Sanskrit Syllable LM Falsification (T7 Redo)",
  "description": "Phase-33 T7 redo: The CORRECTED Phase-32 T7 falsification. Previous T7 used a character-level Sanskrit LM (728K chars, SA assigned all signs to 'a') — methodologically invalid. This redo uses SanskritSyllableLM (424 syllables, 651 bigrams, same granularity as DravidianSyllableLM). Both experiments run WITHOUT anchors for a fair comparison: the SA searches the full 390-sign M77 space against each target LM. If Dravidian (T1) mean_consistency > Sanskrit (T7), the Dravidian hypothesis survives the head-to-head falsification. Null hypothesis H0: Sanskrit fits equally well as Dravidian. Citations: Sanskrit Vedic sources, A.1 (M77).",
